news.title: Pune: Revised Maan Mhalunge town planning scheme gets department nod
news.para: The revised plan was put up before the director of the town planning department as nearly 8.4 hectares of the total 250 hectares was in the flood line area.

news.title: Kolkata civic body allows more time to switch over to new property tax system
news.para: Earlier, the KMC authorities had fixed a December 31 deadline for conversion from a rent-based valuation method to the area-wise (UAA) system and announced an annual 5% penalty for those who won’t convert to UAA.

news.title: Nashik civic body sets Feb 15 deadline for fire audit report submission
news.para: The civic body said that water and power supplies will be snapped and the properties will be sealed if owners fail to submit fire audit reports within the deadline. Moreover, the NMC administration has warned of fines in the range of Rs 20,000 to Rs 50,000.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body seals three commercial properties over tax default
news.para: With the parties concerned ignoring repeated messages, the MC was left with no option but to seal the buildings after completing the legal exercise on Monday.

news.title: Realtors slams Ludhiana development body over delay in issuing of NoCs
news.para: The businessmen are claiming that more than 23,000 NoC applications are pending with Glada since last month and the pendency is increasing day by day.

news.title: UP-RERA logs 23% growth in registration of new real estate projects in 2022
news.para: "Around 258 and 216 projects were registered in 2018 and 2019, respectively, in comparison to 215 projects in 2022. Another 161 and 174 projects were registered in 2020 and 2021, respectively," the state's real estate regulator said in the statement.

news.title: Goa to implement affordable central housing schemes
news.para: The cabinet note said provisions in the regulations allow for relaxation such as minimum plot size, maximum coverage while developing housing for EWS.

news.title: DTCP demolishes four illegal colonies in Farrukhnagar
news.para: District town planner (enforcement) Manish Yadav said illegal colonies had come up on around 20 acres of agricultural land without any permission from the competent authority.

news.title: Soon, dust-control rules for builders in Ahmedabad
news.para: ​The civic body has proposed 15 dust-control rules for construction sites, and will refuse development permissions to sites failing to comply with even one of them.

news.title: Yes Bank-DHFL case: CBI seeks AIIMS board to assess Avinash Bhosale's health
news.para: ​Bhosale was arrested on May 26 last year by the CBI and the Enforcement Directorate later took his custody in a money laundering case. He is currently in judicial custody and has been admitted in a hospital since October.

news.title: Real estate transactions in Dubai hit record high in 2022
news.para: The property boom comes amid an influx of Russians who have purchased properties in some of Dubai's most popular areas, after Moscow faced a tightening of Western sanctions following its invasion of Ukraine.

news.title: New home prices fall again in China in December 2022
news.para: Prices in December declined 0.2% month-on-month, the fifth straight month of decline and the same pace as in November, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data released on Monday.

news.title: China's Country Garden wires funds to repay dollar bond due Tuesday: Source
news.para: Based in the southern city of Foshan, Country Garden is one of the few private developers considered good quality by regulators and has benefited from policy supports to help its liquidity.

news.title: Over 4.02 lakh homes completed in top seven cities in 2022: Anarock
news.para: Approx. 5.44 lakh units are lined up for completion in 2023 across the top seven cities. NCR is expected see highest completions of approximately 1.67 lakh units followed by MMR where about 1,32,900 units are expected to be ready by year-end.

news.title: Anti-pollution curbs under GRAP stage-III lifted in Delhi
news.para: ​Curbs under Stage III included a ban on non-essential construction and demolition, closure of stone crushers and mining activities in Delhi-National Capital Region (NCR).
